### <span id="vii.ii.ix-p0.1"></span>IX. <span id="fr_1762"></span>[1763](#fn_1762.md)

<span id="vii.ii.ix-p2"></span>Taking occasion from Papias of
Hierapolis, the illustrious, a disciple of the apostle who leaned on the
bosom of Christ, and Clemens, and Pantænus the priest of \[the Church\]
of the Alexandrians, and the wise Ammonius, the ancient and first
expositors, who agreed with each other, who understood the work of the
six days as referring to Christ and the whole Church.

